# Quartermaster SOP

[bold]1.[/bold] The Quartermaster must ensure that every approved order is delivered within 15 minutes of having been placed and approved;

[bold]2.[/bold] In the event of a major crisis, such as terrorism, expediency is to be favored over paperwork, as excessive bureaucracy may be detrimental to the well-being of the station;

[bold]3.[/bold] The Quartermaster is [bold]not[/bold] permitted to authorize the ordering of [color=#cb0000]Security[/color] equipment and/or gear without express permission from the [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color] and/or [color=#1b67a5]Captain[/color]. An exception is made during station ending emergencies or terrorism, where said equipment is to be delivered to [color=#cb0000]Security[/color], post-haste;

[bold]4.[/bold] The Quartermaster is permitted to authorize non-departmental orders (such as a [color=#5b97bc]Medical Doctor[/color] asking for Insulated Gloves) without express permission from the respective [color=#1b67a5]Head of Staff[/color] (in this example, the [color=#f39f27]Chief Engineer[/color]), utilizing their best judgement, although they may still request a stamped form. However, any breach of Standard Operating Procedure and/or [textlink="Space Law" link="SpaceLaw"] that results from said order will also implicate the Quartermaster;

[bold]5.[/bold] The Quartermaster is [bold]not[/bold] permitted to authorize the purchase of an HFR Crate without express permission from the [color=#f39f27]Chief Engineer[/color];

[bold]6.[/bold] The Quartermaster is required to follow the guidelines put in place for [color=#b18644]Cargo Technicians[/color];
